style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>To place a new system in the galaxy first select=
 the
type of system from the game editor panel. Then place the new system by
left-clicking with the mouse in the main view.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Note that the new sys=
tem must
not be too close to an existing system, star or gas cloud.<o:p></o:p></span=
></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>The number of planets=
 in the
system is influenced by the star type: Main Sequence, Red Giant and Super G=
iant
stars typically have many planets and moons. White Dwarf and Neutron stars =
only
have one or two planets, but White dwarf stars often have major asteroid
fields.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

